.TH "vga_switcheroo_register_audio_client" 9 "vga_switcheroo_register_audio_client" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vga_switcheroo_register_audio_client \- register audio client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vga_switcheroo_register_audio_client
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "const struct vga_switcheroo_client_ops *ops "  ","
.BI "struct pci_dev *vga_dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
client pci device
.IP "ops" 12
client callbacks
.IP "vga_dev" 12
pci device which is bound to current audio client
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Register audio client (audio device on a GPU). The client is assumed
to use runtime PM. Beforehand, \fBvga_switcheroo_client_probe_defer\fP
shall be called to ensure that all prerequisites are met.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -ENOMEM on memory allocation error, -EINVAL on getting
client id error.
